Comment (src/views/admin/AiDiagnosticsView.vue:523):
The `hash: '#notifications-health-panel'` here doesn't actually open or scroll to the health panel. The router (`src/router/index.ts`) defines no `scrollBehavior`, so vue-router won't scroll to the hash, and `NotificationsView.vue` doesn't read the route hash — its health content sits behind a tab selected by component state (the `panelId: 'notifications-health-panel'` tab), not by the URL hash. So "Open Notifications health" lands on the notifications tab but doesn't surface the health panel the label promises.

Options: add a `scrollBehavior` that honors `to.hash` AND have NotificationsView select the matching tab from the hash, or drop the hash and link plainly to `admin-diagnostics-notifications` so the label matches the behavior.
