Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/AiDiagnosticsView.vue, update the RouterLink in the summary queue card so it no longer claims to open the Notifications health panel via a hash that NotificationsView does not consume. Keep the route name as 'admin-diagnostics-notifications', remove hash: '#notifications-health-panel', and change the link text from 'Open Notifications health' to behaviorally accurate text such as 'Open Notifications'. Do not modify src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue to read hashes for this fix; the recorded design keeps NotificationsView internally unchanged.
Implementation guidance: In src/composables/useAiDiagnostics.ts, remove only the nonexistent 'data.cells.labelSets' entry from labelKeyStopPaths. Leave 'data.scope.labelSets' and 'data.events.metadata' in place so raw label keys such as _policy remain intact in drawer scope and event metadata displays. Do not rename AiDiagnosticsCell.labelSetHashes or add a cell-level labelSets field; the current path is just a no-op stop path.
